OVERVIEW:
    This program generates a provider registration file (.reg) from
    information read from a provider library.

OPTIONS:
    -h, --help                  Print this help message.
    -v, --version               Print version information.
    -n, --namespace NAME        Register provider for this namespace (option
                                may be repeated to specify multiple
                                nsDirs).
    -l, --link                  Mode for developers. Instead of copying library file
                                link is created in lib directory.
    -o, --hosting HOSTING       Use given hosting mode (@requestor@,@inproc@,<user>).

EXAMPLES:
    The following generates a provider registration file for the provider
    contained in 'libDogProvider.so'. It then copies the .reg file and
    the provider to the installed locations.

        $ omireg -n interop -n root/cimv2 libDogProvider.so
